    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-17T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="823"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Russian Issue/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-18T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 18, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 18—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. Department’s 18, January 30, 3 p.m. concerning Russian issue of
                    reorganization loan. Under my instructions Paxton<note n="90" xml:id="d823fn90"
                        >J. Hall Paxton, Second Secretary of Embassy in China, at Nanking.</note>
                    saw Jabin Hsu, Director of Domestic Affairs of the Ministry of Finance, and with
                    my approval has furnished to him copies of the letters dated June 5, 1936 signed
                    by W. E. Hurry and July 15, 1936 signed by Sir Leonard Franklin,<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d823fn91">Letters not printed; see Department’s instruction No. 252,
                        September 5, 1936, <ref target="frus1936v04#pg_595">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1936, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 595</ref>.</note> showing that British
                    bondholders have received 30 percent <pb facs="0673" n="665" xml:id="pg_665"/>
                    of face value stating Hsu promised to look into the matter. Further developments
                    will be reported.</p>
                <p>Copy to Peiping by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
